          <p style="font-size:1.0625rem;color:var(--gray-500);margin-bottom:2rem;line-height:1.7">Our free resume builder helps you create a professional, ATS-optimized resume in minutes. No sign-up required, no hidden fees — just a powerful tool that works entirely in your browser. Whether you're a software engineer, product manager, teacher, nurse, or recent graduate, our builder provides everything you need to land your next role.</p>

          <h3 style="font-size:1.125rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin:2rem 0 0.75rem">Why Use Our Resume Creator?</h3>
          <p>Most free resume builders limit your options or watermark your PDF until you pay. Ours doesn't. You get access to 8 professionally designed templates, each with 7 customizable color themes, for absolutely nothing. Your data never leaves your browser — it's stored in localStorage, not on our servers. You can export your resume as a clean PDF with one click, print it directly, or save your progress and come back later.</p>

          <p>Our builder includes smart features like AI-powered bullet point suggestions that help strengthen your experience descriptions, an ATS readiness score that shows you how well your resume will perform with applicant tracking systems, and a quick-start wizard that builds a first draft from just your job title and skills. You can rearrange sections, toggle visibility for each section, and see every change reflected in a live preview — no switching between tabs to check formatting.</p>

          <h3 style="font-size:1.125rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--gray-900);margin:2rem 0 0.75rem">What Makes a Great Resume in 2025?</h3>
          <p>The job market has changed dramatically in recent years. With 75% of resumes rejected by ATS systems before a human reads them, and recruiters spending an average of 7.4 seconds on initial review, your resume needs to be both machine-readable and human-compelling. The most effective resumes in 2025 share several key characteristics: they're tailored to specific job descriptions, they use strong action verbs with quantified achievements, they follow a clean single-column format, and they include relevant keywords naturally throughout.</p>

          <p>Start with a strong professional summary that hooks the reader in 2-3 sentences. Follow with your work experience, listing 3-5 bullet points per role that showcase specific achievements rather than job duties. Include your education, a comprehensive skills section, and optional sections like certifications, projects, languages, and volunteer work. Every section should serve a purpose — if a detail doesn't strengthen your application, leave it out.</p>

